content_chunks.content: The course introduces the smart city aspect, as well as smart cities and building technologies. It analyses the benefits and challenges of smart buildings. Examples of smart cities around the world are given to better understand smart cities, construction and society and their implementation. The course also covers other topics such as smart cities; construction, the application of smart systems in smart cities and building construction (home automation; health monitoring; assistive objects, etc.).

Smart city and Society 5.0 technology for next-generation urban environments - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in creating intelligent urban ecosystems that integrate advanced technologies for sustainable, human-centered communities. Students master smart city concepts, digital infrastructure development, and Construction 5.0 technologies that enable connected, responsive urban environments. The curriculum covers AI-driven urban planning, circular economy practices, smart energy systems, intelligent farming, and augmented reality applications for cities. Graduates emerge equipped to implement Society 5.0 principles, develop smart mobility solutions, manage urban waste systems, and create resilient, disaster-prepared communities that balance technological advancement with human well-being and environmental sustainability.
